                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 793.94/214.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-01-27T20:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 27, 1915—8 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Further Japanese demands reported today include administrative powers in South
                    Manchuria and special rights respecting the nationalized iron deposits
                    throughout China.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
